* Save Unstructured (Text) Results to RaceRoster.
*
*   When to use:    After the race to publish final unstructured text results.
*   How to use:     Double-click to upload results to RaceRoster.
*
*   Setup:
*     Pass the RaceRoster sub-event ID and destination filename below.
*     Example (direct):  ResultsUnsOnline.rsm   297655   "~results_5k.txt"
*     Example (Entries): ResultsUnsOnline.rsm   %rr_5k_u%   "~results_5k.txt"
*
*   Recommendation:
*     - If you publish both structured and unstructured results, use separate
*       RaceRoster sub-event IDs (e.g. %rr_5k% for structured, %rr_5k_u% for
*       unstructured). Define them once in Entries.INI rather than hardcoding IDs
*       in multiple listings and RSMs — this avoids forgetting to update one file.
*     - Prefix the destination filename with ~ (e.g. "~results_5k.txt"). The tilde
*       creates the file in the race directory; without it, the file is created in
*       the binary directory, which can cause issues when switching races.

ResultsUnsOnline.rsm   %rr_5k_u%   "~results_5k.txt"
